c&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> changed</span><hr size=1> Aye, used to be ye need the skill.  Just to be safe, I'm gonna have a smith friend do it for me, but I keep reading that Verant removed the requirement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=caedebald>Caedebald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 6:28:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~jaddington/elvenpaladin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: changed</span><hr size=1> <br>       My smithing is at &quot;awful&quot; and I had no problem with any of the combines. I think I put one practice point into it at level 8 or something. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>      Hope that helps, good luck!<br><br>      -Caedebald Goldheart<br>      Cavalier of Erollisi Marr of 52 Blessings<br>      Order of the Silver Drakes<br>      Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utormarctruelight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tormarc Truelight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 6:44:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armor of Ro, Smithing Skill?</span><hr size=1> it no longer requires smithing, as a matter of fact, when i made my Breastplate of Ro, i got this message<br><br>You have become better at Blacksmithing (1) <br><br>LOL<br><br>or i got real lucky, but i would hope it doesnt require it, each quest piece cost a minimum of 200pp(for plat bars) as it is without needing to up blacksmithing. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15391>Tormarc Truelight</a><BR>57 Knight<BR>Radiant Eclipse</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoarsiam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coarsiam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 6:58:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armor of Ro, Smithing Skill?</span><hr size=1> hehe thanks very much, YEAH, that's what i wanted to know, that i don't the skill, thx thx thx.<br><br>And you are right, the things to make the Ro-Armor are so expensive and not easy to get that it would be more than bad when they would lack.<br><br>Thx again<br>A really happy 35th Paladin of So|Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 7:23:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armor of Ro, Smithing Skill?</span><hr size=1> I made all the peices of Ro myself, I did not have any smithing skill. Its auto-success, but not trivial so your smithing skill will go up sometimes. Very similar to combining silks into silk swatches, never fails but not trivial until 20. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Baron Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>Crusader for Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=normandy>Normandy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 256<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/30/02 11:31:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armor of Ro, Smithing Skill?</span><hr size=1> # Aye, used to be ye need the skill. Just to be safe, I'm gonna have a smith friend do it for me, but I keep reading that Verant removed the requirement.  #<br><br>The molds are No Drop -- are you going to have your friend do the questing for them too?<br><br>Just do it yourself.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urotep.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rotep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/30/02 1:21:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armor of Ro, Smithing Skill?</span><hr size=1> Hail all!<br><br>Nay, I do not think that you need any smithing skill. But I would also be safe and get your skill up to 1. When I did my brestplate, my smithing skill was 0. I was nervous about it...but it worked perfectly.<br><br>But this is true for Ro armor only...I tried doing another quest for a SV Cold cloak...and it failed on the last 'combine'step (of 32 steps) because my tailoring was under 100. Whoops <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br><br>The Armor of Ro is a very rewarding quest...since you walk away with Warmly faction to every paladin/cleric guild in the old world.<br><br>One question...I've been looking to finish my ro suit, and the sharks are never up it seems. Has anybody seen the Plague Shark in Eruds Crossing lately? Does it still spawn and follow the boat to Erudin? <br><br>Be safe all! <p>Rotep Auragood<br>Human Paladin<br>Lord of Honor - <a target=_blank href=http://www.veratae.cjb.net>Veratae's Blade</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzandorfz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zandorfz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/30/02 1:33:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armor of Ro, Smithing Skill?</span><hr size=1> It has been a few months since I did the Plague sharks, but even then they did not follow the boat.  Mostly they would pop up off the right end of the dock looking out from the beach, down near the bottom (under a cluster of normal sharks).  I think the plague shark may be tied to the killer shark in rotation some how, because at one point I got a killer shark &quot;beached&quot; where it stayed for several days in an un-hittable spot. No more plague sharks until I finally got a GM to nuke the killer shark, then a plague shark spawned within minutes.<br><br>Zandorf<br>53 Paladin<br>Tholuxe Paells<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showPrevMessage?topicID=3490.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showNextMessage?topicID=3490.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3490.topic&index=8><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.emailToFriend?topicID=3490.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.threadControl?topicID=3490.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3490.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3490.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<